Focused Thinking = a concentrated form of thinking
Diffuse Thinking = a relaxed thinking state, one of the brain settles into at resting

- Analogies and metaphors making learning easier
- Looking at things broadly, and see what the options are.

- Able to get to the initial stage of solving the problem. 

- Learn a little bit every day and it will truly help you learn and retain information. The more difficult, the more you have to bounce back and forth between focused and diffused mode of thinking. 
